# Docker-Only Project

This project runs only inside Docker.

## Environment

- Use Node.js 22 LTS.
- Never assume Node.js is installed on the host machine.
- Never assume npm is installed on the host machine.
- Never install packages on the host machine.
- Never execute Node.js commands on the host machine.

## Dependencies

- Add dependencies only through package.json.
- Do not install dependencies manually on the host.
- If a new service is required, update docker-compose.yml.

## Commands

- Run all commands through Docker containers.
- Run tests through Docker containers.
- Run build commands through Docker containers.
- Explain the purpose of a command before suggesting it.

## TypeScript

- Use TypeScript only.
- Enable strict mode.
- Avoid any.
- Prefer interfaces for contracts.
- Use explicit return types for public APIs.

## Architecture

- Follow clean architecture principles.
- Separate domain, application and infrastructure layers.
- Keep modules small and focused.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Document public APIs.

## Testing

- Write tests for business logic.
- Keep tests isolated and deterministic.

## MCP

- Prefer MCP tools over custom shell commands when available.
- Reuse existing MCP servers before creating new ones.
- Keep MCP integrations isolated behind interfaces.

## Code Quality

- Prefer updating existing files over creating unnecessary files.
- Do not introduce dependencies without a clear reason.
- Avoid large files and large classes.
